document_data.History:
As a young man, Dahl studied to be an Oghman paladin. For reasons unclear to Dahl, Oghma revoked his powers and Dahl was kicked out of his order. Dahl moved to [[Waterdeep]] and at some point began working for the Harpers, tracking down antiquities and magical items of interest.<ref>{{Cite digital book/Lesser Evils|?}}

In the {{YearlinkName|1478}}, Dahl was assigned to hunt for antiquities with [[Tam Zawad]], a fellow Harper. While looking around Waterdeep, the pair heard about a page from a magical [[Netheril|Netherese]] tome for sale by a merchant. They were unable to buy the page, but Tam, Dahl and companions stole the page from the mansion of the wealthy caravan master who purchased it.{{Cite digital book/Lesser Evils|2536}}

With the help of Tam's daughter, [[Mira Zawad|Mira]], they were able to locate the lost [[Library of Tarchamus|library]] of [[Tarchamus the Unyielding]], which they explored, finding Tarchamus' magic [[Book of Tarchamus|tome]] the page belonged to. In the process, they destroyed the library and the undead inside.<ref>{{Cite digital book/Lesser Evils|?}}
